\cf0 <p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">In his final semester, Logan covered the 2020 state legislative session as an intern for Idaho Public Radio at the university\'92s McClure Center for Public Policy Research in Boise. He interned concurrently with Idaho Public Television as a production assistant for <em>Idaho Reports</em>.</p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">Alongside veteran capitol reporters, Logan wrote <a href="{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://web.archive.org/web/20260418072956/https://loganfinney.com/idaho-legislature-2020"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 https://web.archive.org/web/20260418072956/https://loganfinney.com/idaho-legislature-2020}}">regular stories</a> for rural newspapers across Idaho. </p><p class="" style="white-space:pre-wrap;">His work at the statehouse was published in the <em>Bonner County Daily Bee</em>, the <em>Coeur d\'92Alene Press</em>, the <em>Idaho County Free Press</em>, the <em>Owyhee Avalanche</em>, the <em>Power County Press</em>, the <em>Aberdeen Times</em>, and online through <em>Idaho Public Radio</em>. </p>\cell \row

